Business Impact Estimation (Life RPG)
Assumptions

To estimate impact, we assume:

Average user has 5–8 daily tasks/habits
Without structure, ~30% tasks are missed or delayed
Each missed task costs ~10–15 minutes of inefficiency later
Active users: 100 users (hackathon demo scale)
Average productive time value: ₹200/hour (~$2.5/hour)

1. Time Saved
Logic:
Tasks per user per day = 6
Missed/inefficient tasks (30%) = ~2 tasks
Time lost per task = 12 minutes

Time wasted per user per day:

2 × 12 = 24 minutes

With Life RPG (assume 60% improvement in consistency):

24 × 0.6 = ~14 minutes saved per day

For 100 users:

14 × 100 = 1400 minutes/day ≈ 23 hours/day saved

Impact: ~23 productive hours saved daily (100 users)

2. Cost Reduction (Productivity Value)

Convert time saved into money:

23 hours/day × ₹200/hour:

= ₹4,600 per day

Monthly (30 days):

₹4,600 × 30 = ₹1,38,000

Impact: ~₹1.3L/month productivity value recovered

3. Revenue Recovery (Missed Opportunities)

Missed tasks = missed opportunities (learning, fitness, work output)

Assume:

10% of tasks are high-value (career, study, income-related)
Missing those reduces potential output by ₹500/user/month

For 100 users:

₹500 × 100 = ₹50,000/month

With Life RPG improving completion by 60%:

₹50,000 × 0.6 = ₹30,000 recovered

Impact: ~₹30K/month in recovered opportunity value

Final Impact Summary
Metric	Impact (100 Users)
Time Saved	~23 hours/day
Cost Reduction	~₹1.38L/month
Revenue Recovered	~₹30K/month
Key Insight (This line is GOLD for judges)

By gamifying consistency, Life RPG converts behavioral inefficiency into measurable productivity gains, turning small daily improvements into significant economic impact at scale.
